model.hed: Photographic Proof That Red Lipstick Is All You Need To Turn Heads
model.dek: Plus more epic beauty looks from London Fashion Week.

items.caption: [New York Fashion Week Spring/Summer 2016](http://www.teenvogue.com/gallery/nyfw-best-beauty-moments) came and went, and with it we saw glittery cat eyes, rhinestone-encrusted face masks, and the prettiest butterfly-inspired shadow, ever. But our days of getting gorgeous beauty ideas are far from over. We’ve now hopped across the pond and entered London Fashion Week territory. So far, it’s clear that the British definitely know how to have fun with color. We’re loving everything from the major lipstick moments, to the move against black eyeliner and into blue territory, to effortlessly mussed, cool-girl strands. Click through to get a dose of British beauty that you should totally import into your hair and makeup routines.

items.title: Burberry
items.caption: Makeup pro, Wendy Rowe, gave the Burberry girls the ultimate moody statement lips for spring. First, she lined the models’ pouts using [Burberry Lip Definer in Oxblood No. 14](https://us.burberry.com/lip-definer-oxblood-no14-p39781151), then used [Burberry Lip Velvet in Oxblood No. 437](https://us.burberry.com/lip-velvet-oxblood-no437-p39897321) for the overall color. Pair this lip look with satin skin, nude eyes and a classic trench, and you’re good to go for the season.

items.title: Burberry
items.caption: Rowe’s tip for nailing a major lip look? Rub a Q-tip around the perimeter to blur the line.

items.title: Giles
items.caption: Giles brought on another gorgeous lip situation, and  this one is red hot! Paired with kohl-rimmed eye liner and tousled, carefree hair, this night-out glamour is as cool as it gets.

items.title: Giles
items.caption: Who better to model a supermodel-worthy look than the ultimate British babe, Georgia May Jagger?

items.title: Erdem
items.caption: Here’s proof that sometimes unexpected shadow colors can look totally refreshing. This all-around orange-y eye moment is daring-yet-surprisingly chic. The inspiration? "Tea-stained eye haunted with a creamy, velvet finish. Skin is moist and windswept, but beautiful,” says makeup artist, Val Garland, for Nars Cosmetics.

items.title: Roksanda
items.caption: Blue is big. At least come spring. Baby blue shadow applied liberally around the lid and under the eye makes the crimped hair moment even more edgy. This might not be for everyday, but any time blue eye makeup is involved, we say go for it.

items.title: Jonathan Saunders
items.caption: If you’re a messy liner kind of girl, might we suggest trading in your basic black for an electric blue? How smoldering do the models backstage at Jonathan Saunders look? Instant badass vibes, achieved.

items.title: Mary Katrantzou
items.caption: For more proof that blue liner can be worn many ways, this partial top and bottom move goes perfectly with floral collage clothing.

items.title: Topshop
items.caption: Ruby red lips, smudgy liner and fluffy accessories are the recipe for chic success in London.

fields.name: Emily Gaynor
fields.bio:
__What sort of advice would you give your 18-year-old self?__ 

I wish I would have known that everything works out in the end and if it didn’t, it most likely wasn’t meant to be. I stressed out over a lot of things—looking back I realize how big a waste of time that is. 

__What’s your favorite Teen Vogue moment?__ 

I have so many amazing *Teen Vogue* memories. I think my favorite was assisting on the Leighton Meester February 2009 cover shoot back when I was an intern. I was obsessed with Gossip Girl, and being on set in the LES with Leighton and Patrick Demachelier was definitely one the highlights of my entire college experience. At one point I had to stop pedestrians from walking into the shot and I remember thinking I’ve made it. Haha.

__Share a funny anecdote from a first job or internship.__ 

On my first day of my first internship, EVER, at *Teen Vogue* my purse hit the elevator alarm and the elevator stopped mid-ride—it was completely packed, too. I was mortified.  

__What beauty product are you loving right now?__

I can’t get enough of the Maybelline Master Kajal black liner. I love kohl-rimmed liner and this one is perfect. I also love that as it wears down you get an even more smudgy, smoky, rock ’n’ roll vibe. It’s basically the gift that keeps on giving. 

__What fashion item seems to always be on your shopping list?__ 

I can never have enough pairs of black jeans, but right now I’m in the market for overalls, culottes and a denim dress. 

__What’s your go-to karaoke song?__ 

"You Oughta Know” by Alanis Morissette, of course. 

__Who’s your favorite model and why?__ 

Well, it’s hard to pick, because I love models. But right now, I’m loving Cat McNeil. She’s confident, quirky and has amazing tattoos. 

__What’s your favorite Instagram to follow (other than Teen Vogue)?__ 

I follow a ton of models that I love, but right now my favorite Instagram is [@theacademynewyork](https://instagram.com/theacademynewyork/). They post really out-there images and quotes. And anything cat-related is always an instant-follow. 

__What’s your favorite meal?__ 

Tacos! All day, every day.
